<title>USA: Saratoga ends alliance with Triarc.</title>
<headline>Saratoga ends alliance with Triarc.</headline>
<dateline>SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. 1997-02-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Saratoga Beverage Group Inc said Monday that it is ending its strategic alliance with Triarc Cos Inc, but that the move  would have no material adverse effect on Saratoga's earnings.</p>
<p>The alliance with Triarc consisted of a $3 million line of credit, a sales and marketing agreement and the issuance of warrants to acquire up to 51 percent of the company of a fully diluted basis.</p>
<p>Triarc exercised warrarnts to acquire 300,000 shares of class A common stock, which represents about 9.9 percent of the outstanding common before the agreement was canceled.</p>
